cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.CR

This paper deals with the problem of automatically verifying program invariants, which is a common topic in software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed approach uses constraint-based reasoning, which is a technique often used in programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The approach also involves dynamic analysis, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with proving or disproving likely invariants, which is a problem that can be formulated as a constraint satisfaction problem (cs.CR).
